- table numbering labels
- table style
- figure style

For each class above:

- perform a full-document pass, not sample inspection
- verify font, size, bold state, spacing, line spacing, indentation, and alignment
- also verify class-specific rules where applicable, such as hanging indent for references, centered layout for captions, three-line-table rules, or image sizing and wrap consistency
- for any class touched by direct paragraph rewriting, also check paragraph-level formatting and run-level formatting separately so residual direct formatting cannot pass unnoticed
- for any class touched by structure-changing edits, re-check the style class after the structural pass even if it was previously repaired

Do not merge adjacent classes just because they appear visually similar. For example, Chinese body text and Latin-script or numeric body text must still be checked separately when the template or school rules distinguish them.

