   - recheck TOC after all class-level fixes
   - run the final machine-vision review
6a. During the final cross-check, record an explicit pass or fail for every touched format class. Do not declare completion if even one touched class is still unverified or still using a mixed format.
6a1. Whenever heading classes were touched, or whenever the user asked for an overall thesis format check, the completion record must explicitly include separate status lines for:
   - level-1 headings
   - level-2 headings
   - level-3 headings
6a2. If the user reports that headings do not match the template, treat that as a failed heading-class review and return to heading-only repair before working on later classes.
6b. Treat these as separate required format classes whenever they appear in the thesis:
   - level-1 headings
   - level-2 headings
   - level-3 headings
   - level-4 headings
   - Chinese body text
   - Chinese abstract title
   - Chinese abstract body
   - Chinese keyword label
   - Chinese keyword content
   - English abstract title
   - English abstract body
   - English `Keywords` label
   - English keyword content
   - TOC title
   - TOC entries
   - references title
   - references body
   - acknowledgements title
   - acknowledgements body
   - figure paragraph
   - figure caption
   - table caption

Rationale:

- front-matter fixes often affect pagination and TOC page references
- heading normalization should happen before body-text cleanup
- figure and table normalization should happen before the final pagination pass
- references and acknowledgements should be checked after the main text is stable
- TOC and final visual review should come last because earlier formatting changes can invalidate them

### Thesis Completion Review

1. After content and format edits are done, perform one machine-vision review pass on the final artifact before declaring completion.
2. The machine-vision review must check requirement fulfillment directly, including chapter completeness, figure-code-effect correspondence, table style such as three-line tables, pagination or layout anomalies, and whether the visible result matches the user's requested changes.
2a. For thesis format repair, the machine-vision review must also compare the final thesis against the school template or approved sample for every touched format class. A class does not pass just because it is internally consistent; it must also be consistent with the template baseline where the template defines it.
3. Chapter-structure review must verify that each major chapter still has its expected terminal summary subsection such as `本章小结`, unless the user or template explicitly removes that requirement.
3a. Chapter-structure review must also verify that every major chapter begins on a new page unless the school template or the user explicitly requires another layout.
4. For every added, replaced, or moved image, the review must verify five things together:
   - the intended image is visibly present
   - the correct numbered caption is visibly present
   - the image and caption still correspond to each other
   - the image does not cover text, captions, tables, or neighboring figures
   - surrounding text does not intrude into the image area
5. On text-heavy pages, the machine-vision review must also verify paragraph semantics: headings must remain standalone heading paragraphs, body text must not merge into heading lines, and first-line indentation must remain consistent with the thesis style.
5a. The machine-vision review must treat each abstract as a block.
   - verify title, body, and keyword line all exist
   - verify `关键词` and `Keywords` were not skipped during formatting repair
   - verify the keyword line did not drift onto a standalone page unless the template explicitly requires it
6. Before declaring completion, run the full `Thesis Format Class Review` and treat it as mandatory, not optional polish.
7. Do not rely on sparse representative-page sampling alone for image-heavy chapters. Perform a per-figure review on all modified figures, and inspect representative text-heavy pages for indentation and heading-boundary regressions.
8. If the machine-vision review cannot clearly recognize a caption, image boundary, image-text relationship, chapter-summary presence, or paragraph-boundary correctness, treat that area as unverified and continue investigating instead of declaring it correct.
9. If the machine-vision review finds unmet requirements or visual defects, continue revising until the review passes.
10. If the thesis uses superscript literature citations or other cross-references, the final review must verify that no citation has degraded into `错误！未定义书签` or `Error! Bookmark not defined`.

11. If the user explicitly asks to verify inserted figures or their positions, machine-vision review is mandatory for every changed figure block. Do not claim the figure is fixed from structure, object counts, insertion logs, or exported-PDF appearance alone.
12. Validation must distinguish structural success from visual success.
   - Structural success means the document objects and paragraph relationships look correct.
   - Visual success means the actual displayed page no longer shows overlap, clipping, burial, detachment, cross-page split, or unreadability.
   - Do not report completion from structural success alone.
13. Do not accept a figure as fixed merely because the image object exists, the caption exists, the image and caption are on the same page, or the exported PDF looks acceptable.
14. For figure-layout defects reported from DOCX or WPS page view, final acceptance must be based on that actual viewing environment or a rendering path proven equivalent to it.
   - Do not treat Word-exported PDF as the final truth when the user’s failure mode is in DOCX or WPS live layout.
   - If the actual viewing environment cannot be verified, mark the result as unverified rather than fixed.
15. A thesis figure passes only if all of the following are true:
   - the intended figure is visibly present in full
   - the figure boundary is clearly visible
   - surrounding text does not cover, cut through, or intrude into the figure area
   - the correct caption is visibly present directly below the figure
   - the figure and caption remain correctly paired
   - the figure and caption stay on the same page
   - the figure remains readable at thesis print scale, not just technically present
15a. A major chapter title passes pagination review only if it begins on a new page, unless the school template or the user explicitly requires another layout.
15b. A table block passes pagination review only if the table caption and the corresponding table start on the same page; if they are split by pagination, that table block is still failing.
16. If any of the following occurs, the figure block is still failing:
   - text covers any part of the figure
   - only a small fragment of the figure remains visible
   - the caption is present but the intended figure is not
   - the figure is present but the caption is missing
   - the caption belongs to the wrong figure
   - the figure is on one page while the caption is on the next page
   - the figure is anchored to body text
   - the rendered result still matches the user-reported failure screenshot
   - a major chapter title appears in leftover space instead of starting from a new page
   - a table caption appears at the bottom of one page while the corresponding table begins on the next page
17. After repairing any figure, run a document-wide figure regression pass.
   - confirm every visible figure caption still has a corresponding visible figure
   - confirm every figure is still in a reasonable location
   - confirm adjacent figures do not swallow each other
   - confirm no later page now has text covering another figure
   - confirm no figure-caption block was split by pagination changes
18. If verification is incomplete, the completion statement must be conservative.
   - Allowed: `structure repaired, actual view not yet verified`
   - Allowed: `PDF output looks correct, DOCX/WPS view not yet verified`
   - Not allowed: `fixed` unless actual visual verification has passed
19. For every changed figure block, verify paragraph boundaries explicitly:
   - image paragraph contains only the image object
   - caption paragraph contains only the caption text
   - the next paragraph is separate body text or a heading
20. Treat any of these as a failed figure block:
   - blank paragraph between image and caption
   - caption merged with body text
   - caption merged with a heading
   - body text visually aligned as though it were part of the caption
21. Verify caption numbering punctuation explicitly against the school template or the user's correction:
   - if the required form is `图1-1` or `表1-1`, do not leave any `图1.1` / `表1.1`
   - update both captions and in-text references together

